headline: 3 Consumer Stocks We Think Twice About
summary: The performance of consumer discretionary businesses is closely linked to economic cycles. This volatility leads to big swings in stock prices that have worked in their favor recently - over the past six months, the industry has returned 18.9% and beat the S&P 500 by 2.8 percentage points.
